Perfect 👍 I’ll update your snippet and replace every ~/... reference so that it will correctly resolve to /MyApp/... (or root / if you deploy at root) when running under IIS.

Here’s the corrected version of your head + script references:

<!-- Custom styles -->
<link href="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Content/styles.css") %>" rel="stylesheet" />

<!-- Existing JS -->
<script src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Scripts/all.min.js") %>"></script>

<!-- Footer scripts -->
<script src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Scripts/scripts.js") %>"></script>
<script src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Scripts/simple-datatables.js") %>"></script>
<script src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Scripts/datatables-simple-demo.js") %>"></script>


---

🔑 Key Fixes

Replaced

<link href="~/Content/styles.css" rel="stylesheet" />

with

<link href="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Content/styles.css") %>" rel="stylesheet" />

Replaced

<script src="~/Scripts/all.min.js"></script>

with

<script src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/Scripts/all.min.js") %>"></script>

Replaced footer script paths (/Scripts/...) with ResolveUrl so they also map correctly to /MyApp/....



---

✅ After this change, your IIS app will no longer try to load files from http://myserver/Content/..., but instead correctly from http://myserver/MyApp/Content/....


