--  
protected void btnLogout_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
        {
            Session.Clear();
            Session.Abandon();

            if (Request.Cookies[".ASPXAUTH"] != null)
            {
                HttpCookie authCookie = new HttpCookie(".ASPXAUTH");
                authCookie.Expires = DateTime.Now.AddDays(-1);
                Response.Cookies.Add(authCookie);
            }

            Response.Redirect("/login.aspx");
        }


---

Good catch 👍
Right now your logout code is using

Response.Redirect("/login.aspx");

That always points to the root of the server (http://myserver/login.aspx) ❌, not inside your app virtual directory (http://myserver/MyApp/login.aspx).


---

✅ Fix: Use ResolveUrl or VirtualPathUtility

Change your redirect like this:

Response.Redirect(ResolveUrl("~/login.aspx"));

or

Response.Redirect(VirtualPathUtility.ToAbsolute("~/login.aspx"));

Both will correctly resolve to:

http://myserver/MyApp/login.aspx

when your app is under /MyApp/.


---

🔑 Final btnLogout_Click Code

protected void btnLogout_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    Session.Clear();
    Session.Abandon();

    if (Request.Cookies[".ASPXAUTH"] != null)
    {
        HttpCookie authCookie = new HttpCookie(".ASPXAUTH");
        authCookie.Expires = DateTime.Now.AddDays(-1);
        Response.Cookies.Add(authCookie);
    }

    // Redirect correctly to app root + login page
    Response.Redirect(ResolveUrl("~/login.aspx"));
}


