---

Nice question 👍 — this is the same problem.

When you write:

<a href="home.aspx">Dashboard</a>

➡️ The browser will look for http://myserver/home.aspx ❌ if you’re not in /MyApp/ context.
It won’t automatically prepend /MyApp/.


---

✅ Fix Options

1. Use ResolveUrl

<a href="<%= ResolveUrl("~/home.aspx") %>">Dashboard</a>

This ensures it always resolves to:

http://myserver/MyApp/home.aspx


---

2. Use runat="server" on the link

ASP.NET will resolve ~ automatically if you add runat="server":

<a runat="server" href="~/home.aspx">Dashboard</a>


---

3. Use asp:HyperLink control (if you prefer server controls)

<asp:HyperLink ID="lnkDashboard" runat="server" 
    NavigateUrl="~/home.aspx" Text="Dashboard" CssClass="breadcrumb-item" />


---

🔑 Your Fixed Breadcrumb

Here’s how I’d fix it (cleanest way without switching to asp:HyperLink):

<ol class="breadcrumb mb-4 mt-3">
    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="<%= ResolveUrl("~/home.aspx") %>">Dashboard</a></li>
    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">Meetings</li>
</ol>


